libuvc
------------------------------------------
libuvc is a cross-platform library for USB video devices, built atop libusb.
It enables fine-grained control over USB video devices exporting the standard
USB Video Class (UVC) interface, enabling developers to write drivers for
previously unsupported devices, or just access UVC devices in a generic
fashion.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.32-1
  libusb1.0-1.0.19-1
  libuvc0-0.0.5-1bl1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.24.51-5
  cmake-2.8.12.2-3
  cygport-0.17.0-1
  gcc-core-4.9.0-1
  make-4.0-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/ktossell/libuvc

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/ktossell/libuvc/archive/v0.0.5.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack libuvc-0.0.5-X-src.tar.xz
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
        unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./libuvc-0.0.5-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libuvc-0.0.5-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libuvc-0.0.5-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libuvc0-0.0.5-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libuvc-devel-0.0.5-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

